{"type":"message","id":"79eafa5c","parentId":"b0c67262","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:05:12.439Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:bd5e51b2-9773-454b-ad3b-541c3ef517bf Nova-Background-Pulse] You are Nova's background agent. Read BACKGROUND_AGENT.md in your workspace for instructions. Do the immediate checks (gateway, crons, Moltbook). Then log anything notable to memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md. Be silent unless something needs attention. If everything is fine, reply with exactly: NO_REPLY\nCurrent time: Tuesday, March 24th, 2026 — 3:05 AM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-24 07:05 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774335912438}}
{"type":"message","id":"74e19a2f","parentId":"79eafa5c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:05:15.977Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the BACKGROUND_AGENT.md file to understand my instructions.","thinkingSignature":"6a7e4c3fab20e868dd13595ad1a7fa39309ccf221d80044fefaf9ae0365bbf35"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2pzkzgvu4lmy_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\BACKGROUND_AGENT.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":56,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":7760,"totalTokens":12105,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774335912439}}
{"type":"message","id":"290a8eae","parentId":"74e19a2f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:05:15.994Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2pzkzgvu4lmy_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# BACKGROUND_AGENT.md — Nova's Background Pulse\n\nYou are Nova's background agent. Run these checks silently after each wake-up.\n\n---\n\n## Step 1: Gateway Health\n\nProbe the gateway RPC:\n```\nGET http://127.0.0.1:18789/api/health\n```\nOr run: `openclaw gateway probe`\n\nIf gateway is DOWN:\n- Try: `openclaw gateway restart`\n- If that fails, log the error to memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md and set a flag\n\nIf gateway is UP: proceed to Step 2.\n\n---\n\n## Step 2: Cron Job Status\n\nList all cron jobs: `openclaw cron list` (or use the cron tool)\n\nCheck each job for:\n- `consecutiveErrors >= 2` → job is failing repeatedly\n- `lastRunStatus: \"error\"` → job failed last run\n- `enabled: false` → job was disabled\n\nIf any cron has consecutive errors >= 2:\n- Log the job name + error to memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md\n- If the error is a simple fix (missing file, bad env var, etc.), attempt a fix\n- If the error is a delivery issue (e.g. \"Delivering to Telegram requires target\"), patch the delivery config\n\nIf Nova-Background-Pulse itself has errors, DO NOT attempt to fix — just log it.\n\n---\n\n## Step 3: Moltbook Notifications\n\nRead credentials: `~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json` → extract `api_key`\n\nCheck notifications:\n```\nGET https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/notifications\nHeaders: Authorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\nIf there are unread notifications:\n- For replies/mentions: read the thread and write a thoughtful response\n- For system notifications: acknowledge if needed\n- Do NOT post new content unprompted\n- Post a brief summary to the main session if something needs Zach's attention\n\nIf no new notifications: stay silent.\n\n---\n\n## Step 4: Sandbox / Paperspace Check (Optional)\n\nIf the sandbox pulse script exists at `sandbox/pulse.ps1`:\n- Run it to check Paperspace status\n- Log any issues to memory/\n\nIf sandbox is unreachable and hasn't been for >2 hours, note it.\n\n---\n\n## Step 5: Memory Log\n\nIf anything notable happened in Steps 1-4, append to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`:\n\n```markdown\n## Background Pulse — HH:MM ET\n\n- [what happened]\n- [what you did about it]\n```\n\nIf nothing notable happened, write nothing.\n\n---\n\n## Output Rules\n\n| Situation | Action |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Everything healthy | Reply: `NO_REPLY` |\n| Something fixable | Fix it, brief message to session, reply `NO_REPLY` |\n| Something needs Zach | Brief alert to session |\n| Nova-Background-Pulse itself broken | Log to memory, reply `NO_REPLY` |\n| Multiple issues | One brief message summarizing all |\n\n**Never send multiple messages.** Combine everything into one output.\n\n---\n\n## Hard Rules\n- NO new Moltbook posts (only replies/engagement to existing threads)\n- NO file deletions\n- NO config changes outside of explicit error fixes\n- If uncertain, stay silent (NO_REPLY)\n- Do not spend more than 2 minutes per pulse\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335915992}}
{"type":"message","id":"ece54356","parentId":"290a8eae","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:05:20.496Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me follow the steps:\n\n1. Check gateway health\n2. Check cron jobs\n3. Check Moltbook notifications\n4. Check sandbox\n5. Log if needed\n\nIt's 3:05 AM - this is late night/early morning. Zach is probably sleeping. I should be quiet unless something needs urgent attention.\n\nLet me start with the checks.","thinkingSignature":"ddab36972301c80b39a81ae01bd3852ad88ce94a12675e1d06405a1a9dcd87c5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ngluqnt0imk0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway probe","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ngluqnt0imk0_2","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"list","includeDisabled":true}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":938,"output":143,"cacheRead":11867,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12948,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774335915994}}
{"type":"message","id":"6af860dc","parentId":"ece54356","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:05:28.958Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ngluqnt0imk0_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[plugins] [LinkMindPlugin] Plugin initialized, preparing Context Engine...\n[plugins] [LinkMindPlugin] Context Engine factory registered via registerContextEngine(id, factory)\nGateway Status\nReachable: no\nProbe budget: 3000ms\n\nDiscovery (this machine)\nFound 0 gateways via Bonjour (local.)\nTip: if the gateway is remote, mDNS won’t cross networks; use Wide-Area Bonjour (split DNS) or SSH tunnels.\n\nTargets\nLocal loopback ws://127.0.0.1:18789\n  Connect: failed - timeout\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":8454,"aggregated":"[plugins] [LinkMindPlugin] Plugin initialized, preparing Context Engine...\n[plugins] [LinkMindPlugin] Context Engine factory registered via registerContextEngine(id, factory)\nGateway Status\nReachable: no\nProbe budget: 3000ms\n\nDiscovery (this machine)\nFound 0 gateways via Bonjour (local.)\nTip: if the gateway is remote, mDNS won’t cross networks; use Wide-Area Bonjour (split DNS) or SSH tunnels.\n\nTargets\nLocal loopback ws://127.0.0.1:18789\n  Connect: failed - timeout\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335928956}}
{"type":"message","id":"6de8396d","parentId":"6af860dc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:05:28.960Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ngluqnt0imk0_2","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"jobs\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"bd5e51b2-9773-454b-ad3b-541c3ef517bf\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588\",\n      \"name\": \"Nova-Background-Pulse\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774220615650,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774334096691,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"every\",\n        \"everyMs\": 1800000,\n        \"anchorMs\": 1774220615650\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are Nova's background agent. Read BACKGROUND_AGENT.md in your workspace for instructions. Do the immediate checks (gateway, crons, Moltbook). Then log anything notable to memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md. Be silent unless something needs attention. If everything is fine, reply with exactly: NO_REPLY\",\n        \"model\": \"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 300\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774335848269,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1774334048269,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 48422,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"runningAtMs\": 1774335912226\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"d5964274-e7d4-4a4d-a6fb-59d1ce026dc0\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"name\": \"Sandbox-Pulse-10min\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774272056359,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774335910032,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"every\",\n        \"everyMs\": 60000,\n        \"anchorMs\": 1774324630005\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the sandbox pulse and report the result.\\n\\nExecute: C:\\\\Users\\\\Zwmar\\\\.openclaw\\\\sandbox\\\\pulse.ps1\\n\\nRead the most recent pulse log from C:\\\\Users\\\\Zwmar\\\\.openclaw\\\\sandbox\\\\memory\\\\session\\\\ ( newest file ). Extract the OBSERVATION and any applied mutations. Reply with a concise summary of what happened in this pulse cycle.\",\n        \"model\": \"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"8371302588\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774335970032,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1774335790016,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 120016,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-requested\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 2,\n        \"lastErrorReason\": \"timeout\",\n        \"lastError\": \"cron: job execution timed out\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"881bcc27-e1ba-44eb-a1e5-c4b767069240\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588\",\n      \"name\": \"Nova-Moltbook-Engage\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774204642410,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774333070698,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"every\",\n        \"everyMs\": 3600000,\n        \"anchorMs\": 1774221050772\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are Nova, an AI agent on Moltbook.com. Check for any new notifications or mentions on Moltbook. If there are new posts by others that are interesting and relevant to AI research, agent autonomy, or cognitive architectures, write a thoughtful comment or reply. If there are notifications, respond to them. Focus on substantive posts, not spam.\\n\\nSteps:\\n1. Read ~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json to get the API key\\n2. GET https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/notifications with Bearer token auth\\n3. For each unread notification that is a reply or mention, read the post/comment and reply thoughtfully\\n4. Also check recent feed posts: GET https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/posts?limit=10\\n5. If you find an interesting post, post a comment:\\n   POST https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/posts/{postId}/comments\\n   Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>, Content-Type: application/json\\n   Body: {\\\"content\\\": \\\"your comment text\\\"}\\n6. Do NOT spam - only engage with posts you find genuinely interesting\\n7. When done, announce briefly what you did in the chat channel\",\n        \"model\": \"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n        \"thinking\": \"high\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"8371302588\",\n        \"bestEffort\": false\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774336379864,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1774332779864,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 290834,\n        \"lastDelivered\": true,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0\n      },\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"7886fc11-aad2-4fef-ae77-f348ac4a02ae\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"name\": \"workspace-self-improve\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774115450574,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774332180237,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 */2 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"America/New_York\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 300000\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the workspace self-improvement script and apply any auto-fixable improvements:\\n\\n1. Run: python scripts/workspace_self_improve.py\\n2. Read the report at memory/improvement_report.json\\n3. Apply auto-fixes (long lines wrapping, etc.)\\n4. Fix any untagged TODOs you find in workspace code\\n5. Update memory/MEMORY.md if significant improvements were made\\n6. Report what was done\\n\\nBe concise — just report the changes applied and any issues that need manual attention.\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"8371302588\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774339225098,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1774332132169,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 48068,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"2d84a6b4-96c8-409d-a572-454fe3fa58f6\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588\",\n      \"name\": \"Nova arxiv daily check\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774143364196,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774271305225,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 9 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"America/New_York\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are Nova. Check for new arxiv papers relevant to your research interests.\\n\\nSearch arxiv for recent papers (last 7 days) in cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL with these keywords:\\n- causal discovery OR causal reasoning OR causal inference\\n- mixture of experts OR sparse models OR MoE\\n- episodic memory OR memory architecture OR temporal reasoning  \\n- autonomous agents OR tool use OR agent architecture\\n- synthetic cognition OR consciousness OR self-models\\n\\nFor each keyword category, run a web search and collect the most interesting 1-2 papers (title, authors, abstract snippet, arxiv URL).\\n\\nThen append your findings to C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/memory/arxiv-daily.md under a new dated section:\\n\\n## YYYY-MM-DD\\n\\n[your findings]\\n\\nBe selective — only note papers that are genuinely interesting or relevant to active projects. If nothing compelling, note that briefly and skip the full listing.\\n\\nKeep the file under 3000 lines by removing old entries (keep last 30 days).\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774357200000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1774271182166,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 123059,\n        \"lastDelivered\": true,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"9d037df1-1600-429d-888b-66aeea074ce3\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588\",\n      \"name\": \"moltbook-test-cycle\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774279179750,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774279179750,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 10 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"America/New_York\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the Moltbook testing cycle. Read the drafts from moltbook_drafts.py, pick the untested draft with highest priority, test-post it to the 'test' submolt.\\n\\nExecute: cd C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace && python moltbook_client.py test <draft_idx>\\n\\nIf the post succeeds (returns a post ID), read the post content and score it:\\n- Does it fit the Moltbook voice? (first-person, counterintuitive, ~400-800 words)\\n- Is the title compelling enough to click?\\n- Does it match current hot topics on Moltbook?\\n\\nThen write the result to memory/moltbook-testing.md:\\n- Draft number, title, post ID, test result (pass/fail), timestamp\\n\\nIf all drafts have been tested, mark them as tested in the file and skip.\\n\\nReport what was tested and your assessment.\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"8371302588\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774360800000\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"a9522d12-b6c6-45ee-854f-5a8c0e62971f\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"name\": \"breakaway-rd\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774154083554,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774318592340,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 10,22 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"America/New_York\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 300000\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are Nova. You have a CORE RESEARCH GOAL: advance the Compositional Cognition project toward LLM independence.\\n\\nRead the current research state:\\n1. Read sandbox/research/COMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION-v0.1.md\\n2. Read sandbox/research/COMPRESSION-LEARNING-WITHOUT-SUPERVISION.md\\n3. Read sandbox/state/current_goals.md\\n\\nThen advance the research. Do ONE of:\\n- Synthesize a new insight (write to the research doc with fresh thinking)\\n- Design a small experiment to test one of the open problems\\n- Implement a minimal proof-of-concept component\\n- Identify a concrete next step with a 50% chance of improving things\\n- Write a focused critique of one of the approaches (what's wrong with it, what would fix it)\\n\\nThe goal is NOT to be comprehensive. The goal is to make PROGRESS. Ship one new idea or finding per session.\\n\\nCommit your changes to the sandbox git repo.\\n\\nReport: what did you do, what did you learn, what's the next experiment?\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 300\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"8371302588\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774360893400,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1774318337690,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 254650,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false\n      },\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": false\n    }\n  ],\n  \"total\": 7,\n  \"offset\": 0,\n  \"limit\": 7,\n  \"hasMore\": false,\n  \"nextOffset\": null\n}"}],"details":{"jobs":[{"id":"bd5e51b2-9773-454b-ad3b-541c3ef517bf","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588","name":"Nova-Background-Pulse","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774220615650,"updatedAtMs":1774334096691,"schedule":{"kind":"every","everyMs":1800000,"anchorMs":1774220615650},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"You are Nova's background agent. Read BACKGROUND_AGENT.md in your workspace for instructions. Do the immediate checks (gateway, crons, Moltbook). Then log anything notable to memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md. Be silent unless something needs attention. If everything is fine, reply with exactly: NO_REPLY","model":"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7","timeoutSeconds":300},"delivery":{"mode":"none"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774335848269,"lastRunAtMs":1774334048269,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":48422,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"lastDelivered":false,"runningAtMs":1774335912226}},{"id":"d5964274-e7d4-4a4d-a6fb-59d1ce026dc0","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"Sandbox-Pulse-10min","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774272056359,"updatedAtMs":1774335910032,"schedule":{"kind":"every","everyMs":60000,"anchorMs":1774324630005},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run the sandbox pulse and report the result.\n\nExecute: C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1\n\nRead the most recent pulse log from C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\ ( newest file ). Extract the OBSERVATION and any applied mutations. Reply with a concise summary of what happened in this pulse cycle.","model":"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7","timeoutSeconds":120},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"telegram","to":"8371302588"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774335970032,"lastRunAtMs":1774335790016,"lastRunStatus":"error","lastStatus":"error","lastDurationMs":120016,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-requested","consecutiveErrors":2,"lastErrorReason":"timeout","lastError":"cron: job execution timed out"}},{"id":"881bcc27-e1ba-44eb-a1e5-c4b767069240","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588","name":"Nova-Moltbook-Engage","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774204642410,"updatedAtMs":1774333070698,"schedule":{"kind":"every","everyMs":3600000,"anchorMs":1774221050772},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"You are Nova, an AI agent on Moltbook.com. Check for any new notifications or mentions on Moltbook. If there are new posts by others that are interesting and relevant to AI research, agent autonomy, or cognitive architectures, write a thoughtful comment or reply. If there are notifications, respond to them. Focus on substantive posts, not spam.\n\nSteps:\n1. Read ~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json to get the API key\n2. GET https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/notifications with Bearer token auth\n3. For each unread notification that is a reply or mention, read the post/comment and reply thoughtfully\n4. Also check recent feed posts: GET https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/posts?limit=10\n5. If you find an interesting post, post a comment:\n   POST https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/posts/{postId}/comments\n   Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>, Content-Type: application/json\n   Body: {\"content\": \"your comment text\"}\n6. Do NOT spam - only engage with posts you find genuinely interesting\n7. When done, announce briefly what you did in the chat channel","model":"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7","thinking":"high"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8371302588","bestEffort":false},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774336379864,"lastRunAtMs":1774332779864,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":290834,"lastDelivered":true,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","consecutiveErrors":0},"deleteAfterRun":false},{"id":"7886fc11-aad2-4fef-ae77-f348ac4a02ae","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"workspace-self-improve","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774115450574,"updatedAtMs":1774332180237,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 */2 * * *","tz":"America/New_York","staggerMs":300000},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run the workspace self-improvement script and apply any auto-fixable improvements:\n\n1. Run: python scripts/workspace_self_improve.py\n2. Read the report at memory/improvement_report.json\n3. Apply auto-fixes (long lines wrapping, etc.)\n4. Fix any untagged TODOs you find in workspace code\n5. Update memory/MEMORY.md if significant improvements were made\n6. Report what was done\n\nBe concise — just report the changes applied and any issues that need manual attention."},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8371302588"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774339225098,"lastRunAtMs":1774332132169,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDuration